eya_def_tools.data_models.general.Organisation
Basic metadata to describe an organisation.
This model is for example used for issuing and receiving organisations of an energy yield assessment.
Attributes: name (str): Entity name of the organisation. abbreviation (Optional[str]): Abbreviated name of the organisation. Default is None. address (Optional[str]): Address of the organisation. Default is None. contact_name (Optional[str]): Name(s) of contact person(s) in the organisation. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.general.TimeResolution
Resolution of time series data.
Attributes: value (float): The value of the time resolution in the specified unit. For example, for 10-minute resolution, the value is '10.0' and the unit is 'minute' unit (TimeMeasurementUnit(StrEnum)): The measurement unit of time in which the time resolution is specified.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.OperationalDataVariable
Reference wind farm operational data variable.
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID of the data variable. This is currently free text but could be replaced by a list of enum options. label (Optional[str]): Optional label of the data variable, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the data variable, which should not be empty if the field is included. This may include clarification of the point of measurement, where relevant. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the data variable, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. data_level (OperationalDataLevel(StrEnum)): Whether the operational data variable is provided for each individual wind turbine ('turbine_level'), is corresponding to or aggregated to the wind farm level ('wind_farm_level') or corresponds to a different ('other') level such as an environmental measurement station. statistic_types (Optional[list[BasicStatisticType(StrEnum)]]): Optional list of the types of statistics included for the data variable.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.OperationalDatasetMetadata
Metadata for a reference wind farm operational dataset.
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID of the reference operational wind farm dataset label (Optional[str]): Optional label of the reference wind farm dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. classification (UnionType[SingleSourceDatasetClassification, DerivedDatasetClassification]): Classification of the type of data and the type of data source. Separate schemas are available to classify unprocessed datasets from a single source, including classification of the data type and source, and datasets that have been derived (aggregated and/or processed, such as operational reports and national databases), including only a classification of the data type as 'derived'. For single source data types (e.g. SCADA) it is meaningful to distinguish between primary and secondary source types, whereas for a derived data type the source type is always secondary. supplying_organisation (Organisation): The organisation that supplied the data. integrity_verification (Optional[str]): Optional description of how the integrity of the data has been and/or can be verified. This field should not be empty if it is included. If any measures were undertaken to verify data integrity, they should always be described here. When this field is omitted, it shall be interpreted to mean that data integrity verification was not undertaken and/or not possible. Default is None. time_resolution (TimeResolution): Time resolution of the operational data. start_date (date): Start of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. end_date (date): End of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. data_variables (list[OperationalDataVariable]): A list of the data variables included in the dataset and used in the assessment. For a large dataset (such as a full wind turbine SCADA dataset) this field should not include all the variables but only the ones that were used in the analysis.

eya_def_tools.utils.doc_utils.eya_def_erdantic.DerivedDatasetClassification
Base pydantic model for the EYA DEF.
This base model includes some adaptations to ``pydantic.BaseModel`` to tune the output JSON Schema as desired.
Attributes: data_type (OperationalDataType(StrEnum)): The type of operational data, categorised as 'derived' for all derived operational datasets (e.g. operational reports or databases with aggregate data). Details of the data type shall be included in the description of the operational dataset, including the type of derived dataset (e.g. an operational report), who produced it (e.g. the turbine OEM) and any relevant details known about how the data were processed. Default is 'derived'. data_source_type (OperationalDataSourceType(StrEnum)): The data source type, which for derived data is 'secondary'. Default is 'secondary'.

eya_def_tools.utils.doc_utils.eya_def_erdantic.SingleSourceDatasetClassification
Base pydantic model for the EYA DEF.
This base model includes some adaptations to ``pydantic.BaseModel`` to tune the output JSON Schema as desired.
Attributes: data_type (OperationalDataType(StrEnum)): The type of operational data, categorised as 'scada' for data from a Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition (SCADA) system, 'metered' for data from a production meter and 'environmental_measurement' for data from an (on-site) environmental measurement station such as a meteorological mast or a remote sensing device (RSD). data_source_type (OperationalDataSourceType(StrEnum)): The type of the operational data source. Primary data, such as primary SCADA data, comes directly from the source without any intermediary. Secondary data covers all other types of data sources, where the data does not come directly from the source, such as secondary SCADA data provided in harmonised form by a data management service provider.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarm
Reference wind farm.
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID for the reference wind farm within the EYA DEF document. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the reference wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the reference wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. wind_farm_id (str): The ID of the wind farm in the 'wind_farms' section of the top-level of the EYA DEF document, containing the configuration data for the reference wind farm. operational_datasets (list[OperationalDatasetMetadata]): List of metadata documents describing the operational datasets from the reference wind farm that were used.
